A New Twist In SSDP Attacks

Arbor ASERT has uncovered a new class of SSDP abuse where naïve devices will respond to SSDP reflection/amplification attacks with a non-standard port. The resulting flood of UDP packets have ephemeral source and destination ports, making mitigation more difficult - a SSDP diffraction attack. This

An Apple a Day: Virtualized Application Service Assurance

As healthcare services, such as electronic medical records (EMR) and radiology services, are increasingly digitized, the need for network and application reliability is becoming a matter of life and death. Further complicating the challenge IT professionals face, more and more healthcare organizations are deploying virtualized network services and adopting “as-a-service” models.
